    <!-- ================================= Compound Bow ==================================== --> 
 
    <ThingDef ParentName="RNMakeableMiscRanged">
    <defName>RN_CompoundBow</defName>
    <label>compound bow</label>
    <description>In modern archery, a compound bow is a bow that uses a levering system, usually of cables and pulleys, to bend the limbs.

In general, compound bows are widely used in target practice and hunting.

The pulley/cam system grants the user a mechanical advantage, and so the limbs of a compound bow are much stiffer than those of a recurve bow or longbow. This rigidity makes the compound bow more energy-efficient than other bows, as less energy is dissipated in limb movement. The higher-rigidity, higher-technology construction also improves accuracy by reducing the bow's sensitivity to changes in temperature and humidity.</description>
